             <lg> 
               <l>A glimpse through an interstice caught,</l>
               <l>Of a crowd of workmen and drivers in a bar-room around the stove late of a winter night, and I </l>
               <l>unremarkâ€™d seated in a corner,</l>
               <l>Of a youth who loves me and whom I love, silently approaching and seating himself near, that he </l>
               <l>may hold me by the hand,</l>
               <l>A long while amid the noises of coming and going, of drinking and oath and smutty jest,</l>
               <l>There we two, content, happy in being together, speaking little, perhaps not a word.</l>
               
               
               
               
               
               
               
               
               
               
               
               
               

         
          
                 
